The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 09 November is 97,885 (11,281.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 04 November, there were 4,324 new confirmed cases (498.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 28 October, there were 4,589 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 6% (265 fewer cases).
